ticles/muybridge.html David Levy, \"Muybridge and the Movies\"], ''Early American Cinema''\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060103000220/http://rhizome.org/object.rhiz?36949 Carola Unterberger-Probst, Animation of the first moving pictures in film history], at Rhizome\n* Burns, Paul. [http://www.precinemahistory.net/1870.htm ''The History of the Discovery of Cinematography: An Illustrated Chronology''], Pre-cinema history\n* [http://www.stephenherbert.co.uk/muy%20links.htm The Compleat Eadweard Muybridge], extensive illustrated bibliography and links\n* [http://www.oac.cdlib.org/findaid/ark:/13030/tf6t1nb6w7/?query=Eadweard%2520lone Lone Mountain College Collection of Stereographs by Eadweard Muybridge, 1867\u20131880] at [[The Bancroft Library]]\n* [http://cdm.bostonathenaeum.org/cdm/landingpage/collection/p16057coll10 Boston Athen\u00e6um: Central America Illustrated by Muybridge. Digital Collection.]\n* {{Gutenberg author | id=Muybridge,+Eadweard | name=Eadweard Muybridge}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Eadweard Muybridge}}\n* [http://cantorcollection.stanford.edu/ Collections search for the Iris & B. Gerald Cantor Center for Visual Arts at Stanford University including the Cantor's Muybridge holdings]\n<!-- Please respect alphabetical order -->\n{{colend|colwidth=26em}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Muybridge, Eadweard}}\n[[Category:19th-century photographers]]\n[[Category:Cinema pioneers]]\n[[Category:Pioneers of photography]]\n[[Category:Stop motion animators]]\n[[Category:1830 births]]\n[[Category:1904 deaths]]\n[[Category:Equine artists]]\n[[Category:English booksellers]]\n[[Category:English cinematographers]]\n[[Category:English inventors]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:Artists from San Francisco]]\n[[Category:People of the California Gold Rush]]\n[[Category:Photographers from San Francisco]]\n[[Category:English people of Dutch descent]]\n[[Category:People acquitted of murder]]\n[[Category:People from 